                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.6176 F 51/220: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-20T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your 35, September 30, 4 p.m. While the Department has no objection to the
                    phrasing of the revised arbitration clause as furnished by Akron, the Department
                    does not care to offer any suggestions inasmuch as it is not a party to the
                    agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
